so disorder and dissolution-as if the very substance of life is its undoing. Rimbaud the Son is now masterfully translated into English, enabling a wide new audience to discover for themselves the author Publishers Weekly called “one of the best-kept secrets of modern French prose."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoets, FrenchxBiographyx19th century. 0aPoets, Frenchy19th centuryvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDeshays, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGladding, Jody, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030017265240uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019907940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300199079423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300199079/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY